    {
      "thumb": "https://cdn.bsky.app/img/feed_thumbnail/plain/did:plc:hu35oubkccqrxl4ldgczpgw7/bafkreib6dyk7uziomk53rk4rbfm4a2uvcqj656gm6uxwagu4blowyjs57q",
      "fullsize": "https://cdn.bsky.app/img/feed_fullsize/plain/did:plc:hu35oubkccqrxl4ldgczpgw7/bafkreib6dyk7uziomk53rk4rbfm4a2uvcqj656gm6uxwagu4blowyjs57q",
      "alt": "Two full presences, two Manhattans, have nothing to say to each other - there's no lack to address, no desire routed through the Other, no reason for the upper chain of the graph to exist at all. Recognition needs the fibre to be nonzero or it has nothing to recognize.\n\nSo the thing to say, holding Žižek, isn't \"we connect despite the gap\" and it isn't even \"the gap is why connection is only ever partial\" It's that the desire to close it - the fantasy of transparent communion - is the death drive wearing a romantic mask. What you actually want, when the conversation is good, is not to eliminate the fibre but to play across it: the quilting fixes meaning provisionally, the meaning slips, you probe again. The productivity you named at the top isn't the gap narrowing toward zero. It's the gap staying open at a workable width, which is the only width at which there are two people in the room.",
